4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, primary elections for
6 offices other than municipal offices are set to occur
7 in May on the Tuesday preceding Memorial Day, except in
8 years when a presidential primary is occurring, in
9 which case the primary election is set for the first
10 Tuesday in March.
11 Also under existing law, a special primary
12 election can be called by the Governor or as provided
13 by law.
14 This bill would require a new special primary
15 election to be held if: (i) the boundaries of one or
16 more legislative or congressional districts to be used
17 in the next general election are changed or altered by
18 either an act of the Legislature or by final order,
19 judgment, or mandate from a state or federal court
20 which permits or requires the use of legislative or
21 congressional district boundaries, and (ii) the change
22 or alteration is made at a time too late to be
23 accommodated during the normal primary election
24 schedule.
25 This bill would specify that the special primary
26 election would only affect those districts impacted by
27 the redistricting.
28 This bill would provide further for the
